Instructions to run the code
Open the terminal in "Part1" directory and enter the make command to compile
The program accepts two optional positional arguments
First Argument is Batch Size to enter and leave the restaurant
Second Argument is minimum number of diners which are coming to the restaurant

The program runs indefinitely without stopping and necessary messages are displayed.
The program can be stopped using Ctrl + C command from keyboard.

Example:
./ass5_1 
    This will run the code with default values of batch size and minimum diners
./ass5_1 10 
    This will run the code with batch size 10 and default value for minimum diners
./ass5_1 10 1000
    This will run the code with batch size 10 and minimum diners as 1000